<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Acceptance Tests — {{FEATURE_NAME}}</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="spec.css">
</head>
<body>
<div class="page-wrap">

  <nav class="sidebar" aria-label="Table of contents">
    <p class="sidebar-title">Contents</p>
    <div id="toc-list"></div>
  </nav>

  <div class="main-content">
    <header class="spec-header">
      <h1>Acceptance Tests — {{FEATURE_NAME}}</h1>

      <table class="meta-table">
        <tbody>
          <tr><th>Feature</th>          <td><code>{{FEATURE_NAME}}</code></td></tr>
          <tr><th>Feature slug</th>     <td><code>{{FEATURE_SLUG}}</code></td></tr>
          <tr><th>Source document</th>  <td><code>{{SOURCE_DOCUMENT}}</code></td></tr>
          <tr><th>Task ID</th>          <td><code>{{TASK_ID}}</code></td></tr>
          <tr><th>Created</th>          <td><code>{{CREATED_DATE}}</code></td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </header>

    <main>

      <section id="purpose">
        <h2>Purpose</h2>
        <p>This document defines acceptance-level test scenarios for the feature.</p>
        <p>These are not necessarily final automated test implementations. They describe the observable behavior that must be true for the feature to be accepted.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>The implementer should use this file to create or update automated tests.</li>
          <li>The reviewer should use this file to verify that the implementation satisfies the approved spec.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <hr>

      <section id="test-strategy">
        <h2>Test strategy</h2>
        <p>The acceptance tests must verify:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>user-facing behavior;</li>
          <li>main success scenarios;</li>
          <li>validation rules;</li>
          <li>edge cases;</li>
          <li>error cases;</li>
          <li>permission / security behavior, if relevant;</li>
          <li>non-goals that must remain unchanged.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 id="testing-style">Testing style configured for this project</h3>
        <pre><code>{{TESTING_STYLE}}</code></pre>

        <h3 id="test-command">Test command</h3>
        <pre><code>{{TEST_COMMAND}}</code></pre>

        <h3 id="test-locations">Related test files or directories</h3>
        <pre><code>{{TEST_LOCATIONS}}</code></pre>
      </section>

      <hr>

      <section id="requirements-coverage-matrix">
        <h2>Requirements coverage matrix</h2>
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Requirement</th><th>Acceptance test(s)</th><th>Covered</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td><span class="req-id">R1</span></td>
              <td>AT1</td>
              <td class="blocking">No</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><span class="req-id">R2</span></td>
              <td>AT2</td>
              <td class="blocking">No</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><span class="req-id">R3</span></td>
              <td>AT3</td>
              <td class="blocking">No</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>

      <hr>

      <section id="acceptance-tests">
        <h2>Acceptance tests</h2>

        <!-- Repeat this card block for each acceptance test. -->
        <div class="card" id="at1">
          <div class="card-header">
            <span class="req-id">AT1</span>
            <span class="card-title">{{TEST_TITLE}}</span>
            <span class="badge badge-draft">Draft</span>
          </div>
          <div class="card-body">
            <dl class="card-fields">
              <dt>Related requirements</dt>  <dd>{{RELATED_REQUIREMENT}}</dd>
              <dt>Scenario</dt>              <dd>{{SCENARIO}}</dd>
              <dt>Preconditions</dt>         <dd>{{PRECONDITION}}</dd>
              <dt>Action</dt>                <dd>{{ACTION}}</dd>
              <dt>Expected result</dt>       <dd>{{EXPECTED_RESULT}}</dd>
              <dt>Negative expectations</dt> <dd>{{NEGATIVE_EXPECTATION}}</dd>
              <dt>Suggested test location</dt><dd><code>{{SUGGESTED_TEST_LOCATION}}</code></dd>
            </dl>
          </div>
        </div>

      </section>

      <hr>

      <section id="edge-case-tests">
        <h2>Edge case tests</h2>
        <p>Use this section for boundary behavior, unusual input, empty states, invalid values, unavailable dependencies, or compatibility cases.</p>

        <div class="card" id="at-edge-1">
          <div class="card-header">
            <span class="req-id edge">AT-EDGE-1</span>
            <span class="card-title">{{EDGE_CASE_TITLE}}</span>
            <span class="badge badge-draft">Draft</span>
          </div>
          <div class="card-body">
            <dl class="card-fields">
              <dt>Related requirements</dt>  <dd>{{RELATED_REQUIREMENT}}</dd>
              <dt>Scenario</dt>              <dd>{{EDGE_SCENARIO}}</dd>
              <dt>Preconditions</dt>         <dd>{{EDGE_PRECONDITION}}</dd>
              <dt>Action</dt>                <dd>{{EDGE_ACTION}}</dd>
              <dt>Expected result</dt>       <dd>{{EDGE_EXPECTED_RESULT}}</dd>
              <dt>Negative expectations</dt> <dd>{{EDGE_NEGATIVE_EXPECTATION}}</dd>
              <dt>Suggested test location</dt><dd><code>{{SUGGESTED_TEST_LOCATION}}</code></dd>
            </dl>
          </div>
        </div>

      </section>

      <hr>

      <section id="error-case-tests">
        <h2>Error case tests</h2>
        <p>Use this section for expected failures.</p>

        <div class="card risk-high" id="at-err-1">
          <div class="card-header">
            <span class="req-id err">AT-ERR-1</span>
            <span class="card-title">{{ERROR_CASE_TITLE}}</span>
            <span class="badge badge-draft">Draft</span>
          </div>
          <div class="card-body">
            <dl class="card-fields">
              <dt>Related requirements</dt>  <dd>{{RELATED_REQUIREMENT}}</dd>
              <dt>Scenario</dt>              <dd>{{ERROR_SCENARIO}}</dd>
              <dt>Preconditions</dt>         <dd>{{ERROR_PRECONDITION}}</dd>
              <dt>Action</dt>                <dd>{{ERROR_ACTION}}</dd>
              <dt>Expected result</dt>       <dd>{{ERROR_EXPECTED_RESULT}}</dd>
              <dt>Negative expectations</dt> <dd>{{ERROR_NEGATIVE_EXPECTATION}}</dd>
              <dt>Suggested test location</dt><dd><code>{{SUGGESTED_TEST_LOCATION}}</code></dd>
            </dl>
          </div>
        </div>

      </section>

      <hr>

      <section id="non-regression-tests">
        <h2>Non-regression tests</h2>
        <p>Use this section to ensure existing behavior is not broken.</p>

        <div class="card" id="at-reg-1">
          <div class="card-header">
            <span class="req-id">AT-REG-1</span>
            <span class="card-title">{{REGRESSION_TEST_TITLE}}</span>
            <span class="badge badge-draft">Draft</span>
          </div>
          <div class="card-body">
            <dl class="card-fields">
              <dt>Existing behavior protected</dt> <dd>{{EXISTING_BEHAVIOR}}</dd>
              <dt>Related requirements</dt>         <dd>{{RELATED_REQUIREMENT}}</dd>
              <dt>Scenario</dt>                     <dd>{{REGRESSION_SCENARIO}}</dd>
              <dt>Preconditions</dt>                <dd>{{REGRESSION_PRECONDITION}}</dd>
              <dt>Action</dt>                       <dd>{{REGRESSION_ACTION}}</dd>
              <dt>Expected result</dt>              <dd>{{REGRESSION_EXPECTED_RESULT}}</dd>
              <dt>Negative expectations</dt>        <dd>{{REGRESSION_NEGATIVE_EXPECTATION}}</dd>
              <dt>Suggested test location</dt>      <dd><code>{{SUGGESTED_TEST_LOCATION}}</code></dd>
            </dl>
          </div>
        </div>

      </section>

      <hr>

      <section id="manual-acceptance-checklist">
        <h2>Manual acceptance checklist</h2>
        <p>Use during human review.</p>
        <ul class="checklist">
          <li><input type="checkbox" disabled> All requirements have at least one acceptance test.</li>
          <li><input type="checkbox" disabled> Main success path is covered.</li>
          <li><input type="checkbox" disabled> Empty state is covered, if relevant.</li>
          <li><input type="checkbox" disabled> Invalid input is covered, if relevant.</li>
          <li><input type="checkbox" disabled> Permission / security behavior is covered, if relevant.</li>
          <li><input type="checkbox" disabled> Non-goals are protected, if relevant.</li>
          <li><input type="checkbox" disabled> Tests are feasible with the current project test setup.</li>
          <li><input type="checkbox" disabled> No acceptance test depends on hidden assumptions.</li>
          <li><input type="checkbox" disabled> Any unresolved behavior is listed in <code>open-questions.html</code>.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <hr>

      <section id="notes-for-claude-code">
        <h2>Notes for Claude Code</h2>
        <div class="claude-note">
          <h4>Rules Claude Code must follow</h4>
          <ol>
            <li>Acceptance tests must map back to <code>requirements.html</code>.</li>
            <li>Do not invent behavior that is absent from the functional brief or approved assumptions.</li>
            <li>If a test requires an unresolved decision, add or update <code>open-questions.html</code>.</li>
            <li>The implementer must create automated tests based on this document where feasible.</li>
            <li>The reviewer must verify that implemented tests cover this document.</li>
            <li>If an acceptance test cannot be automated, mark it clearly and explain why.</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </section>

    </main>
  </div><!-- /.main-content -->
</div><!-- /.page-wrap -->
<script src="spec.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
